# Hexagonal Architecture

Dependencies point **inward**. Handlers depend on ports, not `adapters/postgres`.

## DIP / ISP

| Do | Don't |
|----|-------|
| Depend on narrow `adapters/*` ports via `controllers.Deps` | Import `adapters/postgres` from `controllers/`, `middlewares/`, or `router/` |
| Inject at composition root (`cmd/`, `router/`, `NewDepsFromConfig`) | Construct concrete postgres inside handlers |
| Smallest interface that suffices | Depend on composite `Adapter` when a narrower port works |
| `make mockgen` when ports change | Call `postgres.Load()` outside `integration/` and startup (`cmd/`) |

## Adding a feature (checklist)

1. **Failing unit test (TDD)** ‚Äî see `unit-tests-tdd.mdc`
2. **Port** ‚Äî add/extend interface in `adapters/` if needed
3. **Adapter** ‚Äî implement in `adapters/postgres/` (or other driven adapter)
4. **Handler** ‚Äî methods on focused struct; accept port via constructor/`Deps`
5. **Route** ‚Äî register in `router/`; middleware in `middlewares/` if needed
6. **Mocks** ‚Äî `make mockgen`; unit-test with `adapters/mockgen/`
7. **Integration** ‚Äî `integration/` E2E for HTTP/controller behavior

